1
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:33,080
Let me see clearly.

2
00:02:33,160 --> 00:02:34,760
With a face this ugly…

3
00:02:34,840 --> 00:02:36,400
PREVIOUS EPISODE

4
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:38,840
…you still dare to show up at the event?

5
00:02:38,920 --> 00:02:40,480
Not afraid of scaring everyone?

6
00:02:41,880 --> 00:02:43,600
Are you here to be an extra?

7
00:02:44,760 --> 00:02:46,400
It's called a backup singer.

8
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:54,640
Did you really have to do this to me?

9
00:02:55,640 --> 00:02:56,680
Disqualify Poona!

10
00:02:56,760 --> 00:02:58,600
Disqualify Poona!

11
00:02:58,680 --> 00:02:59,720
Disqualify Poona!

12
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:02,240
All contestants must show sportsmanship.

13
00:03:02,320 --> 00:03:04,720
But if there's bullying like this,

14
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:06,240
I'll disqualify you.

15
00:03:13,320 --> 00:03:16,640
Good. Disqualify her.
We shouldn't let this be an example.

16
00:03:20,640 --> 00:03:21,600
Please calm down.

17
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:31,560
I think before we disqualify anyone,
we should investigate to be sure.

18
00:03:32,320 --> 00:03:34,240
I'm a YouTuber.

19
00:03:34,320 --> 00:03:36,320
Huh? A YouTuber?

20
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:38,880
How's that relevant? Don't listen to him!

21
00:03:40,760 --> 00:03:45,480
I'm asking seriously. Miss Maria,
did you see with your own eyes

22
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:47,640
that Poona put the glass into the shoe?

23
00:03:51,760 --> 00:03:52,920
I didn't see it.

24
00:03:53,920 --> 00:03:56,480
But she handed me the shoes to wear.

25
00:03:58,560 --> 00:04:01,200
You told Poona to pick it up, Maria.

26
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:04,280
If you didn't ask,
she wouldn't have picked it up.

27
00:04:04,840 --> 00:04:07,720
Or is this your plan?

28
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:10,840
- Don't blame others!
- False accusations!

29
00:04:10,920 --> 00:04:13,560
Miss Maria was bullied
and injured like this,

30
00:04:13,640 --> 00:04:15,600
and now you're making false accusations.

31
00:04:15,680 --> 00:04:17,000
- That's not right, Judge.
- Yes.

32
00:04:17,079 --> 00:04:20,279
To accuse someone of wrongdoing,
there must be clear evidence.

33
00:04:22,280 --> 00:04:24,320
If there's no evidence,
you can't make accusations.

34
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:30,760
The evidence is the wound, Mr. Sornrak.

35
00:04:30,840 --> 00:04:32,080
That's right.

36
00:04:32,160 --> 00:04:35,360
Poona definitely put the glass pieces
in my shoes.

37
00:04:35,440 --> 00:04:36,280
Yes.

38
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:38,800
In this case,
Poona should be disqualified.

39
00:04:38,880 --> 00:04:40,560
That's the right thing to do.

40
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:43,240
Alright.

41
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,000
This gentleman is a YouTuber.

42
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:49,680
He took footage behind the scenes.

43
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:54,440
Let's watch and see what the truth is.

44
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:04,880
Yes, I filmed the video.

45
00:05:04,960 --> 00:05:06,320
Let me play it for you.

46
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:07,360
What?

47
00:05:12,440 --> 00:05:13,720
I think it's time

48
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:16,280
for the competition.
If we watch this, we'll waste time.

49
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:18,240
- What do you think?
- Yeah.

50
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:19,560
That's right.

51
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:23,000
I think we should all get ready
for the competition.

52
00:05:23,080 --> 00:05:27,160
Otherwise, we'll miss it.
I won't hold what happened against you.

53
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:30,880
It's just a waste of time
talking about me.

54
00:05:30,960 --> 00:05:34,000
Don't you want to know who bullied you?

55
00:05:34,080 --> 00:05:37,720
Forget it. I'm a good sport.

56
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:39,680
It's just a small thing.

57
00:05:39,760 --> 00:05:42,160
So don't hold a grudge against Poona.

58
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:44,880
Poona.

59
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:47,600
I forgive you.

60
00:05:50,520 --> 00:05:51,840
Mr. Sornrak.

61
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:54,720
Mr. Singha asked me
to take you to the front stage.

62
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:57,520
- It's time for the competition.
- Alright.

63
00:05:59,040 --> 00:06:02,040
Since we're not holding grudges anymore,

64
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:04,640
let's move on and continue. Okay?

65
00:06:04,720 --> 00:06:06,240
Let's not make this into a big deal.

66
00:06:06,320 --> 00:06:08,080
It'll spoil the competition atmosphere.

67
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:11,760
Maria, are you still able to compete?

68
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:14,080
I'm fine now. It doesn't hurt anymore.

69
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:15,360
Great!

70
00:06:15,440 --> 00:06:16,640
I can dance--

71
00:06:16,720 --> 00:06:18,360
Oh, it still hurts a little though.

72
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:21,440
Please, don't post this on YouTube.

73
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:24,920
- Okay, no problem.
- Alright.

74
00:06:25,520 --> 00:06:26,240
Please head outside.

75
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:39,960
Poona, let's get ready.

76
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:41,640
When's your turn?

77
00:06:42,520 --> 00:06:45,080
- I'm number nine.
- We still have enough time.

78
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:48,680
Yes. Teacher, I'll be back in a minute.

79
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:50,280
Sure.

80
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:13,440
There!

81
00:07:13,520 --> 00:07:14,680
He's over there!

82
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:27,000
Hey, follow him!

83
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:32,400
Hey. Hey, stop for a second!

84
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:33,760
What is it?

85
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:37,600
What did you film? Can I see it?

86
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:41,800
Why do you want to see it?
You're not getting disqualified anymore.

87
00:07:42,520 --> 00:07:44,720
I want to know the truth. Who did it?

88
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:53,880
But Mr. Sornrak doesn't want it
to be a big deal.

89
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:58,360
I want to know. Please, let me see it.

90
00:08:01,320 --> 00:08:02,320
If you want to see it…

91
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:05,040
you'll need to pay.

92
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:10,800
You're charging me just to see the video?
Isn't that greedy?

93
00:08:10,880 --> 00:08:12,320
Not paying?

94
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:13,840
No pay, no view.

95
00:08:14,960 --> 00:08:18,840
I thought you were a good person.
Turns out you're just a crook.

96
00:08:18,920 --> 00:08:19,960
Hey.

97
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:24,760
You're not grateful,
and now you're accusing me.

98
00:08:24,840 --> 00:08:28,560
This is defamation, you know?

99
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:32,440
Go wherever you want.

100
00:08:32,520 --> 00:08:33,919
I don't want to see it anymore.

101
00:08:46,640 --> 00:08:49,320
If I let her see it,
she'd probably yell at me.

102
00:08:49,920 --> 00:08:51,960
I forgot to hit record.

103
00:08:53,040 --> 00:08:55,400
I'm just a YouTuber on a mission anyway.

104
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:02,640
It's really him.

105
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:05,440
Wait. Who are you following?

106
00:09:05,520 --> 00:09:06,880
Someone who's already dead.

107
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:09,080
I think you're seeing things.

108
00:09:09,160 --> 00:09:11,160
How can a dead person be around here?

109
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:18,360
Where did he go?

110
00:09:22,640 --> 00:09:23,880
Where is he?

111
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:27,320
There he is!

112
00:09:29,720 --> 00:09:30,960
Hey. Stop!

113
00:09:31,560 --> 00:09:32,560
Hey!

114
00:09:32,640 --> 00:09:33,480
Stop!

115
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:40,720
Who the hell are you?

116
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:45,760
I'm Jan. Please, don't hurt me.

117
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:48,240
Is this the guy you've been looking for?

118
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:51,240
No, he's not.

119
00:09:52,160 --> 00:09:53,960
This is one of Weerachai's men.

120
00:09:54,040 --> 00:09:55,680
You!

121
00:09:58,320 --> 00:09:59,400
Catch him.

122
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,040
Onanong!

123
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:25,720
Where are you?

124
00:10:27,480 --> 00:10:29,920
Don't think you can escape from me.

125
00:10:59,480 --> 00:11:00,520
‪Oh no!

126
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:03,280
Namthip. Phupha.

127
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,520
- Namthip.
- Don't!

128
00:11:23,120 --> 00:11:24,520
Phupha!

129
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:29,920
Found you, Onanong.

130
00:11:32,640 --> 00:11:33,960
Chart!

131
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:40,600
<i>A love triangle between them</i>
<i>is making them fight.</i>

132
00:11:46,800 --> 00:11:48,320
Hey, finish it.

133
00:12:16,880 --> 00:12:20,480
Phupha, it's over for you.

134
00:12:25,840 --> 00:12:27,640
You destroyed my family.

135
00:12:28,680 --> 00:12:30,560
You hurt the people I love.

136
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:33,760
You've made me go through a living hell.

137
00:12:35,760 --> 00:12:38,400
One of us has to die, Chart!

138
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:46,640
DARATHONG COUNTRY MUSIC SINGING CONTEST

139
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:13,600
<i>Riding on a motorbike in a short skirt</i>

140
00:13:13,680 --> 00:13:17,280
<i>It's my business, not anyone else's</i>

141
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:20,520
<i>Talk all you want, you sharp tongue</i>

142
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:24,320
<i>Are you crazy or what?</i>

143
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:26,960
<i>It's the trend these days, darling</i>

144
00:13:31,760 --> 00:13:34,240
Mr. Singha, Boss Nok is here.

145
00:13:37,800 --> 00:13:39,320
Keep an eye on him.

146
00:13:40,560 --> 00:13:41,440
Yes, sir.

147
00:13:41,520 --> 00:13:43,960
<i>It makes my figure look fabulous</i>

148
00:13:44,040 --> 00:13:46,760
<i>Curvy and just right</i>

149
00:13:47,360 --> 00:13:51,560
<i>That's what charm looks like…</i>

150
00:13:52,320 --> 00:13:55,320
Make sure you film the whole song.
Wow, she's really stunning.

151
00:13:57,520 --> 00:14:00,640
Her moves are heart-stopping.
I think she's a clear winner.

152
00:14:02,520 --> 00:14:05,120
You're exaggerating.
Listen to the whole song first.

153
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:08,760
There are plenty
of other good contestants too.

154
00:14:09,440 --> 00:14:10,800
I like her.

155
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:14,480
I want her. I'm picking her.

156
00:14:14,560 --> 00:14:15,840
Hey, stop shaking me!

157
00:14:15,920 --> 00:14:17,880
Go away. You're being annoying.

158
00:14:18,840 --> 00:14:20,600
- Fine, I'll just watch quietly.
- Yeah.

159
00:14:21,960 --> 00:14:24,840
When the lights hit her,

160
00:14:24,920 --> 00:14:27,000
she shines so beautifully.

161
00:14:27,080 --> 00:14:29,920
She truly deserves to be a famous singer.

162
00:14:31,280 --> 00:14:32,120
What's her name again?

163
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:34,800
Her original name was Malee,

164
00:14:34,880 --> 00:14:36,960
but I changed it myself.

165
00:14:37,040 --> 00:14:40,840
Once she enters the industry,
she needs a name like Maria

166
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:44,560
to sound more international.

167
00:14:45,160 --> 00:14:46,880
<i>You boys sure do love to talk</i>

168
00:14:46,960 --> 00:14:50,280
<i>I like my freedom</i>

169
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:53,880
<i>In two days, I'll wear it even shorter</i>

170
00:14:53,960 --> 00:14:57,840
<i>I've got what it takes</i>
<i>That's why I dare to show it</i>

171
00:14:57,920 --> 00:15:04,440
<i>I've got what it takes</i>
<i>That's why I dare to show it</i>

172
00:15:19,680 --> 00:15:21,640
Thank you.

173
00:15:27,120 --> 00:15:29,840
And the song we just heard
was performed by Maria,

174
00:15:29,920 --> 00:15:32,320
the beautiful young lady from Nern Samran.

175
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:35,520
Her performance is absolutely amazing.

176
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:37,720
It melted all of our hearts!

177
00:15:37,800 --> 00:15:40,200
Maria, do you have anything
to say to the judges?

178
00:15:40,880 --> 00:15:44,160
My dream has always been to be a singer
since I was a child.

179
00:15:44,240 --> 00:15:47,280
I want to bring happiness to everyone.

180
00:15:47,800 --> 00:15:49,640
Now, my dream

181
00:15:49,720 --> 00:15:52,480
is in the hands of the judges.

182
00:15:52,560 --> 00:15:54,640
And I hope all of you

183
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:56,880
will support me.

184
00:15:56,960 --> 00:15:58,000
Thank you.

185
00:15:58,080 --> 00:16:01,520
Let's give a round of applause
to support Maria!

186
00:16:03,880 --> 00:16:09,720
She's charming, has a great voice,
and shows respect.

187
00:16:09,800 --> 00:16:13,880
Judges, with all that,
she deserves a perfect score!

188
00:16:21,360 --> 00:16:23,600
- Tu.
- Yes, Boss?

189
00:16:23,680 --> 00:16:25,200
You see the singers in this contest?

190
00:16:25,280 --> 00:16:27,280
They are pretty good.

191
00:16:28,680 --> 00:16:30,200
Which one do you like, Boss?

192
00:16:30,280 --> 00:16:32,720
Just invite them to join our music label.

193
00:16:34,200 --> 00:16:35,360
It's not that hard.

194
00:16:42,560 --> 00:16:44,080
Excuse me.

195
00:16:44,760 --> 00:16:47,320
Are you a contestant?

196
00:16:47,400 --> 00:16:49,640
What time do you perform,
and when exactly?

197
00:16:49,720 --> 00:16:52,160
I need to know.
Oh, that's a nice handbag you have!

198
00:16:54,480 --> 00:16:55,840
I'm not a contestant.

199
00:16:56,800 --> 00:16:59,440
I'm Kamnan Pong's personal secretary.

200
00:17:00,920 --> 00:17:05,079
I see. No wonder you look so stunning.

201
00:17:05,160 --> 00:17:07,240
If you ever want to become a singer,

202
00:17:08,119 --> 00:17:09,359
just let me know.

203
00:17:13,079 --> 00:17:14,640
Okay, I'll excuse myself now.

204
00:17:16,240 --> 00:17:17,520
Okay.

205
00:17:18,119 --> 00:17:21,040
- Aren't you giving me your number?
- Tu!

206
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:23,240
You can't just flirt like that!

207
00:17:23,319 --> 00:17:26,079
Do you want me to take a bullet
for Kamnan Pong?

208
00:17:26,160 --> 00:17:28,000
She's his secretary!

209
00:17:29,600 --> 00:17:30,680
Am I the one in the wrong?

210
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:36,320
Hey, do you know?

211
00:17:37,240 --> 00:17:41,920
I've had Singha steal singers
from me before.

212
00:17:42,720 --> 00:17:45,560
Today, I'm going to do the same.

213
00:17:46,440 --> 00:17:48,920
Alright, next up.

214
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:52,280
Let's hear from our next contestant.
Please welcome

215
00:17:53,400 --> 00:17:55,640
the multi-talented singer,

216
00:17:55,720 --> 00:17:57,760
Poona, from Nern Samran!

217
00:18:26,320 --> 00:18:29,920
Sir, the next contestant is Poona.

218
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:34,240
If you'd like me to do anything,
just let me know. I'll handle it.

219
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:38,680
Got it.

220
00:18:46,560 --> 00:18:47,800
What are you thinking about?

221
00:18:47,880 --> 00:18:49,960
- What?
- Why are you smiling?

222
00:18:57,800 --> 00:18:59,280
‪Look at you.

223
00:19:18,200 --> 00:19:20,440
- Manat, hold the camera for me.
- Where are you going? Bathroom?

224
00:19:20,520 --> 00:19:23,000
Yeah, I'll be right back.
Take the mic too.

225
00:19:25,880 --> 00:19:28,120
Alright, I got it. I'll film.

226
00:19:28,760 --> 00:19:31,320
- That's great.
- Amazing.

227
00:19:31,840 --> 00:19:33,680
- Hey, you.
- Sorry, I wasn't paying attention.

228
00:19:33,760 --> 00:19:35,160
Hey, dull face!

229
00:19:35,920 --> 00:19:36,880
Does saying sorry make it better?

230
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:40,080
If Boss Nok, my boss, got knocked down
like that and ended up crippled,

231
00:19:40,160 --> 00:19:43,080
lying in bed, drooling, unable to move,
with his lower body paralyzed,

232
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:45,240
who's gonna be responsible?
Who's going to take care of me?

233
00:19:45,320 --> 00:19:47,000
- Tu!
- Yes, Boss?

234
00:19:47,080 --> 00:19:49,360
Are you worried about me,
or are you cursing me?

235
00:19:49,440 --> 00:19:51,560
- You jerk!
- Both.

236
00:19:52,920 --> 00:19:57,160
<i>I've waited</i>

237
00:19:57,240 --> 00:20:01,920
<i>Waited so long</i>
<i>My heart unwavering and full</i>

238
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:07,280
<i>But he's forgotten</i>

239
00:20:07,360 --> 00:20:13,320
<i>Forgotten me, with no certainty at all</i>

240
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:15,520
<i>I wait for him</i>

241
00:20:15,600 --> 00:20:18,440
<i>But he forgets I'm waiting</i>

242
00:20:18,520 --> 00:20:24,560
<i>Waiting and pleading</i>
<i>With this lonely heart</i>

243
00:20:28,240 --> 00:20:32,760
<i>Still waiting</i>

244
00:20:32,840 --> 00:20:38,000
<i>I kept hoping until I grew weary</i>

245
00:20:38,600 --> 00:20:42,440
<i>Still waiting</i>

246
00:20:42,520 --> 00:20:48,440
<i>For that heartless one</i>
<i>Crying day and night</i>

247
00:20:48,520 --> 00:20:53,680
<i>He forgot his promise</i>
<i>Leaving this sad country girl behind</i>

248
00:20:53,760 --> 00:20:58,200
<i>Waiting for him</i>

249
00:20:58,280 --> 00:21:00,920
<i>Waiting for him alone…</i>

250
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:03,200
Dad, is something wrong?

251
00:21:06,480 --> 00:21:07,840
Who picked the song for the singer?

252
00:21:08,640 --> 00:21:10,760
- I did.
- Hey.

253
00:21:11,680 --> 00:21:14,560
This song is what made
Onanong Wongwichian famous.

254
00:21:15,360 --> 00:21:16,800
She's the ex-lover of Kamnan Pong.

255
00:21:18,680 --> 00:21:19,920
Don't bring this song up again.

256
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:22,240
Yes, Dad.

257
00:21:23,480 --> 00:21:28,480
<i>A pile of dry firewood and withered straw</i>

258
00:21:28,560 --> 00:21:32,320
<i>Melancholic, just like us…</i>

259
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:33,800
I never thought

260
00:21:34,760 --> 00:21:37,200
Poona would sing this song.

261
00:21:37,280 --> 00:21:40,200
I was the one who recommended
this song to her.

262
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:44,960
I knew Kamnan Pong really liked it.

263
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:53,560
You must really love Kamnan Pong.

264
00:22:03,280 --> 00:22:04,240
Yes.

265
00:22:07,960 --> 00:22:09,400
Kamnan Pong

266
00:22:10,240 --> 00:22:12,080
is the only man I've ever loved.

267
00:22:20,120 --> 00:22:23,040
<i>I kept hoping until I grew weary</i>

268
00:22:23,760 --> 00:22:27,720
<i>Still waiting</i>

269
00:22:27,800 --> 00:22:32,560
<i>For that heartless one</i>
<i>Crying day and night…</i>

270
00:22:32,640 --> 00:22:34,000
Her voice is really good.

271
00:22:37,800 --> 00:22:39,320
What are they doing?

272
00:22:40,080 --> 00:22:41,800
Why just let her sing?

273
00:22:42,600 --> 00:22:44,000
How's the voice? Is it good?

274
00:22:44,080 --> 00:22:46,840
- Her voice is amazing!
- I can't compete with that.

275
00:22:46,920 --> 00:22:48,160
That's true.

276
00:22:48,240 --> 00:22:53,000
<i>Seeing dry leaves fall and wither</i>

277
00:22:53,080 --> 00:22:57,080
DARATHONG COUNTRY MUSIC SINGING CONTEST

278
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:10,880
It's me.

279
00:23:13,720 --> 00:23:15,400
Here it is. This one has to be it.

280
00:23:15,480 --> 00:23:16,440
Really?

281
00:23:16,960 --> 00:23:19,840
With all these wires plugged in like that,
how could it not be?

282
00:23:19,920 --> 00:23:23,320
There are wires everywhere.
How do we know which one is which?

283
00:23:23,400 --> 00:23:25,880
Just follow me. I'll tell you which one.

284
00:23:25,960 --> 00:23:29,200
Are you an electrician?
Were you ever an electrician?

285
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:32,040
I used to be an electrician's wife.
Is that enough?

286
00:23:32,680 --> 00:23:35,000
I also know which wire to pull

287
00:23:35,080 --> 00:23:36,440
to make Poona lose points.

288
00:23:36,520 --> 00:23:37,800
In that case, pull it.

289
00:23:37,880 --> 00:23:39,120
- Go on.
- Hey.

290
00:23:39,200 --> 00:23:42,640
I'm a small woman, like a fire ant.
How am I supposed to pull it?

291
00:23:42,720 --> 00:23:45,240
You do it. I'll tell you which wire.

292
00:23:45,320 --> 00:23:46,920
Do you really know which one?

293
00:23:49,040 --> 00:23:51,440
This one. Today's Monday,
so it's the yellow wire.

294
00:23:51,520 --> 00:23:53,320
If it's Wednesday,
then it must be the green one.

295
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:55,440
There are two colors.
Just pull the yellow one.

296
00:23:56,040 --> 00:23:58,240
Here, you pull it.

297
00:23:58,320 --> 00:24:00,800
I'll keep an eye out.
Once I give the signal, you pull it.

298
00:24:00,880 --> 00:24:02,560
- Is that so?
- Yeah.

299
00:24:02,640 --> 00:24:03,760
I'll wait.

300
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:10,920
Should I pull it?

301
00:24:28,040 --> 00:24:29,240
- Hey.
- What?

302
00:24:29,320 --> 00:24:31,080
- Pull it!
- What?

303
00:24:37,160 --> 00:24:38,840
- Pull it!
- What?

304
00:24:51,360 --> 00:24:52,520
What happened?

305
00:24:53,920 --> 00:24:55,240
Why did the lights go out?

306
00:24:56,680 --> 00:24:57,840
Hey.

307
00:25:11,680 --> 00:25:13,280
‪Joey, are you alright?

308
00:25:24,800 --> 00:25:26,120
Joey!

309
00:25:36,800 --> 00:25:39,480
We're still alive!

310
00:25:41,320 --> 00:25:43,520
We're still alive!

311
00:25:48,840 --> 00:25:50,120
Poona!

312
00:25:50,760 --> 00:25:53,760
Poona, sing live! Sing it!

313
00:26:00,840 --> 00:26:02,200
With the power out,

314
00:26:03,840 --> 00:26:05,840
how can the sound be good?

315
00:26:06,680 --> 00:26:09,840
It has to be Maria.

316
00:26:09,920 --> 00:26:12,240
Only she can be the singer tonight.

317
00:26:19,160 --> 00:26:22,920
<i>He's forgotten</i>

318
00:26:25,520 --> 00:26:30,040
<i>Forgotten about us</i>

319
00:26:30,120 --> 00:26:33,080
<i>Leaving me heartbroken</i>

320
00:26:36,200 --> 00:26:38,720
<i>Waiting for so many years</i>

321
00:26:40,160 --> 00:26:42,760
<i>Now he has a new lover</i>

322
00:26:44,240 --> 00:26:45,160
Hey.

323
00:26:45,680 --> 00:26:50,120
Even without music,
Poona's voice still captivates everyone.

324
00:26:50,720 --> 00:26:53,880
This is the voice with magic.

325
00:26:54,480 --> 00:26:57,760
<i>Deceiving, making me wait</i>

326
00:26:58,880 --> 00:27:05,600
<i>Deceiving, making me wait</i>

327
00:27:18,000 --> 00:27:18,680
JUDGE

328
00:27:32,040 --> 00:27:33,440
Her voice is really good.

329
00:27:38,880 --> 00:27:41,160
What's going on here?
What's happening to everyone?

330
00:27:48,040 --> 00:27:50,320
Damn you, Poona.

331
00:27:52,440 --> 00:27:53,160
‪A ghost!

332
00:27:55,320 --> 00:27:56,920
I'm not a ghost.

333
00:27:58,080 --> 00:28:00,480
I'm Sophie.

334
00:28:05,040 --> 00:28:05,920
A ghoul!

335
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:09,040
It's not a ghoul. It's Joey.

336
00:28:10,560 --> 00:28:13,360
What did you idiots do?
Why do you look like this?

337
00:28:14,480 --> 00:28:17,280
Joey made the electricity shock us.

338
00:28:18,320 --> 00:28:21,440
I didn't! The electricity
shocked us by itself.

339
00:28:22,600 --> 00:28:25,200
Idiot! Useless!

340
00:28:25,280 --> 00:28:28,640
You're the useless one!
Who says they're married

341
00:28:28,720 --> 00:28:30,200
to an electrician?

342
00:28:30,280 --> 00:28:32,040
Neither of you is any good!

343
00:28:32,120 --> 00:28:34,800
Did you hear how loud the applause was?

344
00:28:34,880 --> 00:28:36,120
Huh?

345
00:28:43,520 --> 00:28:44,680
Poona!

346
00:28:47,680 --> 00:28:50,000
Ladies and gentlemen,
I'm waiting for the scores

347
00:28:50,080 --> 00:28:52,160
from our esteemed panel of judges.

348
00:28:52,240 --> 00:28:56,120
In just a moment,
we'll know who will be the winner

349
00:28:56,200 --> 00:28:57,960
and the new singer

350
00:28:58,040 --> 00:29:00,800
for Darathong Music.
The score results will be in my hands

351
00:29:01,400 --> 00:29:04,360
in just a moment. And now,

352
00:29:04,440 --> 00:29:06,840
the results are in my hands.

353
00:29:09,120 --> 00:29:10,360
Sathu.

354
00:29:11,400 --> 00:29:15,840
Please, let Poona win. If she does,
I'll skip fermented fish for a month.

355
00:29:18,440 --> 00:29:21,560
And the winner of today's singing contest…

356
00:29:21,640 --> 00:29:22,480
DARATHONG MUSIC

357
00:29:22,560 --> 00:29:25,040
She is the beautiful lady
from Nern Samran.

358
00:29:27,840 --> 00:29:29,120
JUDGE

359
00:29:35,840 --> 00:29:36,920
The winner is…

360
00:29:46,800 --> 00:29:50,120
Poona, with the song
"Wait for Him to Forget".

361
00:29:59,120 --> 00:30:02,040
My daughter sings way better than this,
with more lighting.

362
00:30:03,560 --> 00:30:06,520
How can she win
without the lights, judges?

363
00:30:39,120 --> 00:30:40,800
Maria only got second place.

364
00:30:44,800 --> 00:30:48,680
Now, may I invite Kamnan Pong,
the president of Darathong Music,

365
00:30:48,760 --> 00:30:50,320
and Mr. Sornrak Darathong

366
00:30:50,400 --> 00:30:52,720
to present the award
and the bouquet of flowers to our winner?

367
00:30:52,800 --> 00:30:54,040
Let's give them a round of applause!

368
00:30:59,760 --> 00:31:02,200
- Hello. Congratulations!
- Thank you.

369
00:31:05,160 --> 00:31:06,400
Hand me the trophy first.

370
00:31:07,320 --> 00:31:09,720
Hand me the trophy. Congratulations.

371
00:31:09,800 --> 00:31:10,840
Thank you.

372
00:31:10,920 --> 00:31:12,520
Let's give her a round of applause!

373
00:31:23,080 --> 00:31:24,600
- Hey, Tu. Tu!
- Yes?

374
00:31:24,680 --> 00:31:26,840
I'm right here. What's up?

375
00:31:26,920 --> 00:31:27,760
I want this one.

376
00:31:28,360 --> 00:31:29,480
This one's awesome.

377
00:31:37,360 --> 00:31:38,600
‪FIRST PRIZE 10,000 BAHT

378
00:31:42,600 --> 00:31:44,920
Please welcome Mr. Sornrak
to present the bouquet of flowers.

379
00:32:03,680 --> 00:32:05,640
Darathong Music is happy to welcome you.

380
00:32:07,120 --> 00:32:08,240
Thank you.

381
00:32:12,680 --> 00:32:14,920
Poona won! She won!

382
00:32:16,840 --> 00:32:19,680
If that's the case,
everything's falling into place.

383
00:32:20,600 --> 00:32:23,800
Poona will be the one
to help us reveal the truth.

384
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:28,240
In no time.

385
00:32:32,120 --> 00:32:33,720
You're good too.

386
00:32:51,440 --> 00:32:53,800
Let's take a picture over there. Go ahead.

387
00:33:09,960 --> 00:33:14,800
Joey, you'll regret this
when we get back home.

388
00:33:14,880 --> 00:33:19,320
How could you let a dark-lit singer
beat my daughter?

389
00:33:19,400 --> 00:33:20,880
Geez.

390
00:33:21,480 --> 00:33:23,440
Let's take plenty of photos.
Smile for the cameras.

391
00:33:35,120 --> 00:33:35,960
Judges.

392
00:33:36,960 --> 00:33:41,120
How could you let a dark-lit singer
win over one with the spotlight?

393
00:33:41,760 --> 00:33:44,960
I'll sue! Sue! I'm hiring a lawyer!

394
00:33:46,920 --> 00:33:49,680
Look at you, all puffed up!

395
00:33:49,760 --> 00:33:51,120
Your Pincher Poona

396
00:33:51,720 --> 00:33:52,880
won first place.

397
00:33:53,520 --> 00:33:56,480
My Maria only got second.

398
00:33:57,840 --> 00:34:00,760
Hey, Pincher Poona's not mine!

399
00:34:00,840 --> 00:34:02,000
Don't say things like that.

400
00:34:05,480 --> 00:34:06,640
You don't feel anything, do you?

401
00:34:09,440 --> 00:34:11,719
- I don't.
- Well, fine.

402
00:34:12,239 --> 00:34:15,000
Let's go. The event's over. Let's leave.

403
00:34:22,120 --> 00:34:24,639
Good job, Pincher Poona!

404
00:34:38,800 --> 00:34:41,360
First, let's go collect the prize money.

405
00:34:48,679 --> 00:34:50,760
Let's go wait for Poona at the car.

406
00:34:56,840 --> 00:34:58,400
Let's go, Teacher.

407
00:34:59,160 --> 00:35:01,240
Hey, hold on.

408
00:35:01,320 --> 00:35:03,040
Wait a minute, beautiful.

409
00:35:03,880 --> 00:35:07,840
My name is Boss Tu. No, I'm just Tu.

410
00:35:08,440 --> 00:35:10,400
My boss is Boss Nok.

411
00:35:10,920 --> 00:35:12,560
He loves your voice so much.

412
00:35:13,160 --> 00:35:14,320
Well…

413
00:35:14,400 --> 00:35:17,880
He has a little something… Hey!

414
00:35:18,400 --> 00:35:21,600
A small gift to give you… Hey!

415
00:35:21,680 --> 00:35:23,080
Don't interrupt!

416
00:35:23,160 --> 00:35:24,000
- From…
- Tu!

417
00:35:25,920 --> 00:35:27,160
Yes, Boss.

418
00:35:27,760 --> 00:35:30,200
- Please go ahead.
- Sweetheart.

419
00:35:31,320 --> 00:35:34,400
In all my 35 years,

420
00:35:34,480 --> 00:35:37,440
I've never seen anyone
as beautiful as you.

421
00:35:38,040 --> 00:35:39,240
It's 65. You're 65.

422
00:35:39,320 --> 00:35:40,400
Hey!

423
00:35:41,920 --> 00:35:44,320
- She sang beautifully, Boss.
- What?

424
00:35:45,240 --> 00:35:46,080
You said she's beautiful.

425
00:35:46,160 --> 00:35:49,240
I've never heard anyone
sing as beautifully as you.

426
00:35:50,560 --> 00:35:51,600
Like nectar.

427
00:35:51,680 --> 00:35:54,520
Your voice is like nectar.

428
00:35:54,600 --> 00:35:57,080
- Truly amazing.
- Truly amazing.

429
00:35:57,160 --> 00:35:58,920
- You mean my voice?
- No!

430
00:35:59,760 --> 00:36:00,680
Not your voice, Uncle!

431
00:36:02,480 --> 00:36:03,480
Enough!

432
00:36:05,160 --> 00:36:08,320
Here, a little gift

433
00:36:08,400 --> 00:36:10,000
from my heart.

434
00:36:15,160 --> 00:36:19,040
Come closer. Blessings to you.

435
00:36:19,640 --> 00:36:21,960
May your spirit be with you.

436
00:36:22,040 --> 00:36:24,640
Just hanging the garland
gives me goosebumps.

437
00:36:25,960 --> 00:36:27,960
I don't even want to imagine.

438
00:36:29,480 --> 00:36:30,440
It's a lot.

439
00:36:31,920 --> 00:36:33,560
I'll treat you to dinner today.

440
00:36:34,920 --> 00:36:35,760
‪Let’s go.

441
00:36:46,960 --> 00:36:48,000
<i>What's going on, Chart?</i>

442
00:36:49,040 --> 00:36:51,320
I saw Phupha at the event, Boss.

443
00:36:53,200 --> 00:36:54,720
Are you drunk or something?

444
00:36:54,800 --> 00:36:56,360
I haven't had any alcohol.

445
00:36:57,240 --> 00:37:00,640
No, this can't be.

446
00:37:02,440 --> 00:37:04,760
The incident happened 20 years ago.

447
00:37:04,840 --> 00:37:06,640
And the body was confirmed.

448
00:37:06,720 --> 00:37:10,240
I'll bring Phupha here to show you.

449
00:37:12,960 --> 00:37:14,040
It's impossible.

450
00:37:15,080 --> 00:37:17,440
He can't come back from hell.

451
00:37:17,520 --> 00:37:18,600
No way, Phupha.

452
00:37:19,320 --> 00:37:22,280
Uncle, I won!

453
00:37:22,360 --> 00:37:23,400
Wow!

454
00:37:24,560 --> 00:37:26,560
You did it! I'm so proud of you.

455
00:37:26,640 --> 00:37:30,280
I'm going to be a singer now.
My dream is finally coming true!

456
00:37:30,920 --> 00:37:34,280
Just a little more, dear.
You'll be an artist with your own songs.

457
00:37:36,320 --> 00:37:40,440
Aunt Wilai, did you hear me sing
when the lights went out?

458
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:43,520
Yes! When Poona sang live,

459
00:37:44,120 --> 00:37:46,760
everyone was speechless!

460
00:37:48,280 --> 00:37:50,200
- Really?
- I heard it.

461
00:37:50,800 --> 00:37:53,280
Your live voice,
anyone who hears it will fall in love.

462
00:37:55,120 --> 00:37:57,280
You're really talented.

463
00:38:01,120 --> 00:38:03,000
Let's walk a bit further.

464
00:38:03,080 --> 00:38:04,520
I think he hasn't gone anywhere yet.

465
00:38:04,600 --> 00:38:06,160
Even if he's a ghost,

466
00:38:06,240 --> 00:38:08,840
I'll kill him again. Phupha.

467
00:38:16,280 --> 00:38:17,840
It seems like he's looking for someone.

468
00:38:19,200 --> 00:38:20,160
They look suspicious.

469
00:38:21,280 --> 00:38:22,240
Let's follow them.

470
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:30,200
But after you join Darathong Music,

471
00:38:30,280 --> 00:38:32,440
you have to be very careful.

472
00:38:33,520 --> 00:38:37,800
And don't forget the promise we made.

473
00:38:40,120 --> 00:38:44,240
Yes, I'll make sure
to bring that teddy bear out.

474
00:38:48,320 --> 00:38:51,360
I'll help you reveal the truth.

475
00:38:54,120 --> 00:38:55,640
Poona.

476
00:38:55,720 --> 00:38:58,760
Whatever you do, your safety comes first.

477
00:39:00,080 --> 00:39:03,360
If anything happens to you,
I won't be able to live on.

478
00:39:06,480 --> 00:39:10,440
Don't worry, Uncle.
I'll make sure I'll be fine.

479
00:39:14,320 --> 00:39:16,720
Let's not worry about revenge for now.

480
00:39:17,320 --> 00:39:20,480
Let's celebrate
that Poona's going to be a singer!

481
00:39:21,080 --> 00:39:23,120
Poona! Poona!

482
00:39:23,200 --> 00:39:25,480
- Poona!
- Poona!

483
00:39:32,520 --> 00:39:33,640
Everyone, get down!

484
00:39:35,800 --> 00:39:38,320
- They're shooting!
- Let's go!

485
00:39:45,480 --> 00:39:47,640
Don't go! It's too dangerous.

486
00:39:48,800 --> 00:39:51,400
Don't worry. I'll lead them that way.

487
00:39:52,000 --> 00:39:53,120
Please take care of Poona.

488
00:39:53,200 --> 00:39:54,640
But it's too dangerous.

489
00:39:55,240 --> 00:39:57,640
I promise, I'll be fine.

490
00:40:06,360 --> 00:40:08,160
Hey, follow him!

491
00:40:09,760 --> 00:40:12,320
Don't be afraid, dear. Mom's right here.

492
00:40:12,840 --> 00:40:15,040
I won't let anyone hurt you.

493
00:40:28,640 --> 00:40:29,960
Poona!

494
00:40:30,040 --> 00:40:33,360
Help Uncle Tharin! They're chasing him
and shooting in that direction!

495
00:40:35,200 --> 00:40:37,440
- Take care of Poona.
- Be careful.

496
00:40:40,360 --> 00:40:42,280
I think you two should leave this place.

497
00:40:43,000 --> 00:40:43,920
But Uncle…

498
00:40:44,000 --> 00:40:46,560
It's okay. Chaiya's gone after him.
They'll handle it.

499
00:40:47,960 --> 00:40:50,720
Please, do what he says. If we stay here,

500
00:40:50,800 --> 00:40:52,240
you might be in danger.

501
00:40:55,160 --> 00:40:56,040
Come out!

502
00:40:58,040 --> 00:40:59,880
I told you to come out!

503
00:41:32,720 --> 00:41:34,760
Who the hell are you?

504
00:41:53,600 --> 00:41:55,520
- This is bad.
- Over here, Captain.

505
00:41:55,600 --> 00:41:56,720
Let's go.

506
00:42:01,360 --> 00:42:03,040
There he is! He's here!

507
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:05,160
Let's go! Get in the car!

508
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:07,280
Hurry, dear!

509
00:42:14,280 --> 00:42:15,720
Go straight home, no stops.

510
00:42:15,800 --> 00:42:17,080
I'll go help Chaiya.

511
00:42:17,680 --> 00:42:18,640
Thanks so much.

512
00:42:20,320 --> 00:42:21,760
- Let's go, everyone.
- Yes.

513
00:42:37,720 --> 00:42:39,840
Hey, stop! Stop right now!

514
00:42:47,320 --> 00:42:49,360
Chart!

515
00:42:49,880 --> 00:42:52,520
- What?
- Don't shoot. That's the police!

516
00:42:52,600 --> 00:42:53,720
We should run.

517
00:42:53,800 --> 00:42:55,240
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

518
00:43:00,000 --> 00:43:01,760
- Hurry, Chaiya!
- Let's go!

519
00:43:03,040 --> 00:43:04,440
They've already run away.

520
00:43:04,960 --> 00:43:08,440
Don't worry, Captain.
I've got a contact. I'll have them follow.

521
00:43:16,800 --> 00:43:18,440
Hello? What's up, Uncle Sergeant?

522
00:43:19,280 --> 00:43:21,800
- Au, where are you?
- I'm guarding the van of Chart's guys.

523
00:43:22,400 --> 00:43:26,200
Good. They're heading that way.
Follow them.

524
00:43:26,280 --> 00:43:29,000
Got it, Uncle. I'll handle it!

525
00:43:29,840 --> 00:43:31,360
Get in the car!

526
00:43:32,400 --> 00:43:33,440
Run!

527
00:43:35,920 --> 00:43:36,840
Hurry!

528
00:43:39,360 --> 00:43:42,080
Go ahead if you can get away. Come on.

529
00:43:42,160 --> 00:43:45,480
Wait, who's that? Who's covering my head?

530
00:43:46,680 --> 00:43:48,080
Ugh, wrong side of the helmet!

531
00:43:58,280 --> 00:43:59,400
Follow them, Sergeant.

532
00:44:23,960 --> 00:44:24,960
This warehouse looks suspicious.

533
00:44:25,040 --> 00:44:27,760
There could be something
we're looking for inside.

534
00:44:31,680 --> 00:44:32,520
Yes, Mr. Kitti?

535
00:44:33,240 --> 00:44:34,560
This is the moment. Let's go!

536
00:44:42,760 --> 00:44:45,080
What's going on, Chart?
Who were you shooting at?

537
00:44:45,880 --> 00:44:48,400
<i>It was Phupha. I followed him.</i>

538
00:44:48,480 --> 00:44:52,200
But someone came to help him,
so I shot at them.

539
00:44:52,280 --> 00:44:53,800
The police arrived just in time.

540
00:44:54,760 --> 00:44:57,760
Are you sure it was Phupha?

541
00:44:59,920 --> 00:45:03,000
I'm sure. His appearance, everything.

542
00:45:03,080 --> 00:45:04,360
I think it has to be him.

543
00:45:04,440 --> 00:45:07,280
We'll catch him first,
then we'll deal with it.

544
00:45:10,000 --> 00:45:11,280
Chart,

545
00:45:12,000 --> 00:45:14,600
he just confirmed it's really Phupha.

546
00:45:17,040 --> 00:45:19,360
It's been almost 20 years.

547
00:45:20,080 --> 00:45:21,480
How could he have survived?

548
00:45:21,560 --> 00:45:22,720
Unbelievable.

549
00:45:23,240 --> 00:45:25,720
Or is it Tharin, his twin brother?

550
00:45:25,800 --> 00:45:29,600
But if Phupha really survived,

551
00:45:31,200 --> 00:45:33,720
I'll send him back to hell myself.

552
00:45:50,200 --> 00:45:51,560
They won't be free for long.

553
00:45:58,080 --> 00:45:59,280
Excuse me, Captain.

554
00:46:00,640 --> 00:46:01,680
Just got back, Sergeant?

555
00:46:03,200 --> 00:46:04,600
Don't even ask, Captain.

556
00:46:04,680 --> 00:46:07,560
I've been guarding the warehouse
all night. I'm so tired!

557
00:46:08,840 --> 00:46:10,120
Any progress?

558
00:46:10,200 --> 00:46:11,440
Uncle Sergeant and Captain Tom

559
00:46:11,520 --> 00:46:14,640
found a chemical storage
hidden in the warehouse.

560
00:46:14,720 --> 00:46:16,000
Right now, Captain Tom

561
00:46:16,080 --> 00:46:17,920
is working on getting a search warrant.

562
00:46:25,560 --> 00:46:26,480
I'll go see Uncle Sergeant.

563
00:46:30,440 --> 00:46:31,400
You're leaving me again, Captain.

564
00:46:37,560 --> 00:46:38,760
Dad!

565
00:46:42,480 --> 00:46:46,280
Dad, I won't allow it.
Poona can't be a singer before me!

566
00:46:46,360 --> 00:46:47,680
Right.

567
00:46:47,760 --> 00:46:49,560
Do whatever it takes
for me to be a singer before her.

568
00:46:49,640 --> 00:46:51,160
- True.
- Otherwise, I'll run away from home!

569
00:46:51,920 --> 00:46:52,760
I'm coming with you.

570
00:46:55,920 --> 00:46:59,520
Juab, can I stay at your house?

571
00:46:59,600 --> 00:47:02,440
Of course! No problem at all.

572
00:47:02,520 --> 00:47:03,880
No, you can't!

573
00:47:03,960 --> 00:47:08,000
How can you stay with him?
Do you know what kind of person he is?

574
00:47:08,080 --> 00:47:09,920
No way, you know?

575
00:47:10,000 --> 00:47:11,280
Hey, Joey!

576
00:47:11,360 --> 00:47:13,040
Hand me my love.

577
00:47:13,760 --> 00:47:14,600
Your lover?

578
00:47:15,600 --> 00:47:16,760
Gun!

579
00:47:18,720 --> 00:47:19,560
Hurry up!

580
00:47:20,760 --> 00:47:21,800
What's taking so long?

581
00:47:21,880 --> 00:47:23,160
Geez.

582
00:47:23,240 --> 00:47:24,640
Wait!

583
00:47:25,240 --> 00:47:26,760
Are you really going to shoot?

584
00:47:26,840 --> 00:47:28,800
I'm not involved in this!

585
00:47:28,880 --> 00:47:31,000
How can you not be involved?

586
00:47:31,080 --> 00:47:33,800
You've been charming
my daughter, haven't you?

587
00:47:33,880 --> 00:47:36,040
I haven't! I'm not charming anyone.

588
00:47:37,560 --> 00:47:38,640
Don't accuse me of that.

589
00:47:39,400 --> 00:47:42,640
By the way, is my coffee ready?

590
00:47:43,360 --> 00:47:44,840
I'm in a hurry today.

591
00:47:44,920 --> 00:47:46,960
In a hurry? Why didn't
you come yesterday then?

592
00:47:47,040 --> 00:47:47,920
What?

593
00:47:48,000 --> 00:47:49,680
I'm angry now! No more coffee for you.

594
00:47:50,360 --> 00:47:52,560
No coffee? What does that
have to do with me?

595
00:47:53,160 --> 00:47:55,400
If you're not selling coffee today,
I don't want it.

596
00:47:55,480 --> 00:47:56,480
I'll come back another time.

597
00:47:58,960 --> 00:48:00,120
Dad!

598
00:48:00,200 --> 00:48:02,360
Do you understand?
I can't lose to that Poona!

599
00:48:02,440 --> 00:48:04,840
- Right.
- She already won.

600
00:48:04,920 --> 00:48:06,320
What do you want me to do?

601
00:48:06,400 --> 00:48:07,880
It's you, Village Head.

602
00:48:07,960 --> 00:48:09,080
You had us do something stupid.

603
00:48:09,160 --> 00:48:12,480
Look what happened.
Poona definitely got sympathy votes.

604
00:48:12,560 --> 00:48:13,720
What did I have you do?

605
00:48:13,800 --> 00:48:16,680
You told us to unplug the power
when she was singing!

606
00:48:18,360 --> 00:48:20,480
Yes, that day, you told us
to unplug the power,

607
00:48:20,560 --> 00:48:23,000
and we got shocked! That day!

608
00:48:23,960 --> 00:48:25,600
So, you're saying it was my fault?

609
00:48:26,200 --> 00:48:28,160
Yes, it's your fault, Dad!

610
00:48:28,240 --> 00:48:31,960
Do whatever it takes for me
to be a singer before Poona.

611
00:48:32,040 --> 00:48:34,560
Or I'll run away from home
and never come back!

612
00:48:35,280 --> 00:48:37,040
I'm coming with you!

613
00:48:38,800 --> 00:48:40,240
Her mother's blood runs deep!

614
00:48:40,320 --> 00:48:41,760
It really runs deep!

615
00:48:44,840 --> 00:48:47,280
I think, since she won,

616
00:48:47,360 --> 00:48:48,920
it means she must have cheated.

617
00:48:49,000 --> 00:48:50,960
- Yes.
- How did she cheat?

618
00:48:51,040 --> 00:48:53,800
She might have used dark magic
on the judges.

619
00:48:53,880 --> 00:48:55,000
Exactly.

620
00:48:55,080 --> 00:48:56,240
Dark magic? Are you crazy?

621
00:48:56,320 --> 00:48:58,680
It's because you two
turned off the lights.

622
00:48:58,760 --> 00:49:00,120
Instead of her dying,

623
00:49:00,200 --> 00:49:03,360
she came back stronger.
Everyone's enchanted by her voice.

624
00:49:03,440 --> 00:49:05,640
Think before you act!

625
00:49:05,720 --> 00:49:08,320
Was it harsh? Yes, it was.
But I don't mind,

626
00:49:08,400 --> 00:49:11,400
because it's all your father's idea.

627
00:49:11,480 --> 00:49:13,280
If you're going to blame someone,
blame your father.

628
00:49:13,880 --> 00:49:15,920
Sophie! Are you saying my father
has no brains?

629
00:49:16,720 --> 00:49:17,560
Yes.

630
00:49:19,880 --> 00:49:21,600
Honestly, he probably doesn't have any.

631
00:49:22,920 --> 00:49:24,960
Sophie!

632
00:49:25,040 --> 00:49:26,240
I'm not involved.

633
00:49:26,320 --> 00:49:27,560
Both of you!

634
00:49:37,000 --> 00:49:40,480
NEXT EPISODE

635
00:49:45,520 --> 00:49:47,880
Is this jar of fermented fish ruined too?

636
00:49:52,000 --> 00:49:52,880
Are you really giving it to me?

637
00:49:55,120 --> 00:49:58,360
<i>I want to be famous</i>
<i>Can’t stand it anymore</i>

638
00:49:58,440 --> 00:50:01,840
<i>I want people</i>
<i>To scream for me at the stage</i>

639
00:52:03,160 --> 00:52:05,240
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
